BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 800.00 Tm (Data Flow and Business Logic) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 778.00 Tm (The user enters filter values on the selection screen. The report reads purchase order data) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 762.00 Tm (from EKKO and EKPO, vendor information from LFA1, material descriptions from MAKT, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 746.00 Tm (schedule line dates from EKET. The program enriches the dataset in internal tables and) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 730.00 Tm (prepares it for ALV display.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 710.00 Tm (Status logic is applied item by item. If the deletion indicator is set, the report shows) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 694.00 Tm (Deleted. If delivery is completed, it shows Completed. If no schedule line exists, it shows) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 678.00 Tm (No Schedule. Otherwise the delivery date is compared with the current system date to) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 662.00 Tm (determine Overdue, Due Soon, or On Time.) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 642.00 Tm (The vendor scorecard aggregates item-level data by vendor number, counting distinct POs,) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 626.00 Tm (summing net values, and computing on-time delivery percentages. The delivery tracker) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 610.00 Tm (calculates days remaining until delivery \(negative values indicate overdue\) and assigns) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 594.00 Tm (urgency levels for quick prioritization.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 48.00 574.00 Tm (Unique Points) Tj ET
BT /F1 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 50.00 552.00 Tm (- Balanced complexity for an ABAP capstone: practical, working, and explainable.) Tj ET
